{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pullrequests/94/comments/16363998.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pull-requests/94/_/diff#comment-16363998"}}, "parent": {"id": 16351294, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pullrequests/94/comments/16351294.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pull-requests/94/_/diff#comment-16351294"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 94, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pullrequests/94.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pull-requests/94"}}, "title": "Fix coverity issues"}, "content": {"raw": "I would prefer keeping the unique pointers and disabling the C4251. I liked Herb Sutter's suggestion from a cppcon video to use smart pointers so you never have to call delete. Disabling the C4251 warnings is a [common response in PIMPL code](http://stackoverflow.com/a/32098634).\n\n@ocrave sorry to drag you into a philosophical debate", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I would prefer keeping the unique pointers and disabling the C4251. I liked Herb Sutter's suggestion from a cppcon video to use smart pointers so you never have to call delete. Disabling the C4251 warnings is a <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/a/32098634\" rel=\"nofollow\">common response in PIMPL code</a>.</p>\n<p>@ocrave sorry to drag you into a philosophical debate</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-28T19:09:03.528115+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod